      • topWithListsNatural

        public GridDefinitionBuilder topWithListsNatural(List<List<String>> data)
        Assumes that the outer list is dimensions and the inner list is the contents of a row, such as a simple data structure for the 'top' axis. For example, the incoming data may be: 
         [                FY18][                FY18][                FY19]
 [                 Jan][                 Feb][                  Q1]
        It will be transformed into: 
         [                FY18][                 Jan]
 [                FY18][                 Feb]
 [                FY19][                  Q1]
        And it will therefore be suitable for us with topWithLists(List), which is the actual implementing method
        Parameters:
        data - the data
        Returns:
        a value
